post_text:
Dear LG Vikings,

I want to invite and strongly encourage everyone to tune into this afternoon's historic SpaceX astronaut launch from NASA's Kennedy Space Center in Cape Canaveral, Florida.

The mission, called DEMO-2, will launch NASA astronauts Bob Behnken and Doug Hurley into orbit on a Crew Dragon spacecraft atop a Falcon 9 rocket. Liftoff is set for 4:33 p.m. EDT (about 1:30 p.m. our time).

You'll be able to watch the SpaceX launch live here and on Space.com's homepage, courtesy of NASA TV, beginning at 12 p.m. EDT (9:00 a.m. our time).

Who knows...maybe someday we'll be watching one of YOU launch into orbit on a NASA spacecraft!!!

#smallschoolBIGdreams

Mr. B

SPACE.COM
Space.com: NASA, Space Exploration and Astronomy News

post_text:
Good Morning LG Community,

Merced County Public Health is offering COVID-19 testing to any Merced County resident at the Merced County Fairgrounds from 7:00 AM to 7:00 PM.

In order to get tested, you must call (888)634-1123 to obtain a patient ID number. Once you have received your patient ID number you can go to the fairgrounds the following day with your ID number and CA driver's license. There is no physician's order necessary to get tested.

You may also register online at: LHI.care/COVID19testing

post_text:
The ACES program wants to continue enrichment during distance learning! We have come up with weekly competitions that everyone can participate in. This weeks challenge is making a blanket fort. You will have the opportunity to win a gift card to Pizza Factory, Savemart, Dollar General, or McDonalds! Please send pictures of your blanket fort to 209-917-6071. Winners will be announced the Monday following the week of the challenge.

Blanket Fort

All you need is a blanket or sheet, chairs and maybe something heavy to sheet in place.
Drape sheet over chairs or over your bed and 2 chairs.
This is very easy to clean up. Have fun!

post_text:
Greetings LG Community! I am very happy to announce that the Bible Christian Church of Le Grand will be providing groceries for our community once again from 9:00AM to 10:00AM this Saturday. There is no registration. The church is asking that everyone stay in their car and the trunk will be loaded by their workers. Workers will be wearing gloves and masks. Anyone walking will be turned away.

Please share this message with as many people in our community as possible and help make this a safe and successful distribution. There will be cereal, milk, meat, pasta, and canned goods.

God bless you and stay healthy and safe.

Sincerely,

Mr. Borba

Good Morning LG Family,

I am VERY happy to announce that our incredible cafeteria staff would like to continue providing much-needed meals over Easter Break for our scholars.

In order to allow these incredible ladies some time with their families and to celebrate Good Friday and Easter Sunday, we will NOT be serving meals on Friday, April 10th (Good Friday) or Monday, April 13th (Easter Monday) only. Breakfast and lunch service will resume as normal on Tuesday, April 14th from 8:00-9:30 AM.

Just another example of how much the folks at Le Grand Elementary care about our kids and our community! Thank you Minnie, Socoro, Jennifer, Ashlee, Josie, and Debbie!!!

Mr. Borba
#wearelegrand

Le Grand Community,

The federal government has waived the requirement that children need to be present to pick up breakfast and lunch during the COVID-19 outbreak. Please send one healthy person to the school to pick up daily meals between 8:00-9:30 AM for your students between the ages of 2-18 years old.

If you are unable to access this valuable resource, please reply back to this message with your reason why. Me and my team will continue to work on your behalf within our current resources to provide support for your family.

Stay safe, stay healthy, stay home...we miss you all!!!

Sincerely,

Mr. Borba
#wearelegrand

post_text:
Dear Le Grand Community,

It's only been one day and I know I speak for everyone here...we miss your kids! I know your child's teacher has been contacting you and keeping you up-to-date with schedules, work, and resources to assist you in keeping your scholars sharp over this temporary school closure.

Tomorrow, Friday, March 20th will be the last day to come and pick up packets and devices in the office. After Friday, the facility will be closed to the public with the exception of our morning meal program.

During this closure, a small skeleton staff will remain on campus to make sure bills are paid, lawns are mowed, food is served, and the campus is monitored and kept safe.

We can't wait to return to normal operations. Until then, please stay safe, stay healthy, keep your kids busy and keep our community, our state, our country, and our entire world in your thoughts and prayers.

Sincerely,

Mr. Borba
#wearelegrand
